cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.MOB, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the performance of 5G networks on smartphones and analyzes handoff mechanisms and app performance over 5G. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses how Internet server selection affects end-to-end performance for 5G users. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper examines app performance (web browsing and HTTP download) over 5G. 
- cs.MOB (Mobile Computing) is another possible category as the paper focuses on 5G performance on smartphones. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly discuss security or cryptography, but it may be relevant in the context of analyzing the security of 5G networks.
